To develop an advanced Angular application that performs input validation, character counting, and character frequency analysis, follow these steps:

1. Set up the Angular project by running the following command in your terminal:
   ```
   ng new character-analysis-app
   ```

2. Change the current working directory to the project folder:
   ```
   cd character-analysis-app
   ```

3. Create a new Angular component called "CharacterAnalysis" using the CLI command:
   ```
   ng generate component CharacterAnalysis
   ```

4. Open the "character-analysis.component.html" file and replace the existing code with the following template:
   ```html
   <div>
     <h1>Character Analysis</h1>
     <label for="input">Input:</label>
     <textarea id="input" [(ngModel)]="inputText"></textarea>
     <button (click)="analyzeInput()">Analyze</button>
     <div *ngIf="errorMessage" class="error-message">
       {{ errorMessage }}
     </div>
     <div *ngIf="result">
       <h2>Character Count: {{ characterCount }}</h2>
       <h2>Character Frequency:</h2>
       <ul>
         <li *ngFor="let char of characterFrequency">
           {{ char }}
         </li>
       </ul>
     </div>
   </div>
   ```

5. Open the "character-analysis.component.ts" file and replace the existing code with the following component logic:
   ```typescript
   import { Component } from "@angular/core";

   @Component({
     selector: "app-character-analysis",
     templateUrl: "./character-analysis.component.html",
     styleUrls: ["./character-analysis.component.css"]
   })
   export class CharacterAnalysisComponent {
     inputText: string = "";
     errorMessage: string = "";
     result: boolean = false;
     characterCount: number = 0;
     characterFrequency: { [char: string]: number } = {};

     analyzeInput(): void {
       this.errorMessage = "";
       this.characterCount = 0;
       this.characterFrequency = {};

       // Input validation
       const hasSpecialCharacters = /[ `!@#$%^&*()_+\-=\[\]{};':"\\|,.<>\/?~]/;
       const hasSpaces = /[\s]/;

       if (hasSpecialCharacters.test(this.inputText) || hasSpaces.test(this.inputText)) {
         this.errorMessage = "Invalid input. Special characters and spaces are not allowed.";
         return;
       }

       // Character count
       this.characterCount = this.inputText.length;

       // Character frequency analysis
       for (let char of this.inputText) {
         if (this.characterFrequency[char]) {
           this.characterFrequency[char]++;
         } else {
           this.characterFrequency[char] = 1;
         }
       }

       this.result = true;
     }
   }
   ```

6. Open the "app.component.html" file and replace the existing code with the following template:
   ```html
   <app-character-analysis></app-character-analysis>
   ```

7. Start the Angular development server using the following command:
   ```
   ng serve
   ```

8. Open your web browser and navigate to `http://localhost:4200`. You should see the Character Analysis application.

Now, when the user enters input in the text area and clicks the "Analyze" button, the application will validate the input for special characters and spaces. If the input is valid, it will display the character count and character frequency analysis. If the input is invalid, it will show an appropriate error message.

Make sure to customize the styling of the application according to your preferences by modifying the "character-analysis.component.css" file.
